<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-01-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-01-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="990" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d990">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Lee</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-01-24"><hi rend="italic">January 24,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="italic">Maine</hi> has been ordered. Will probably arrive at
                            Havana some time to-morrow. Can not tell hour; possibly early. Cooperate
                            with authorities for her friendly visit. Keep us advised by frequent
                            telegrams.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>